etymology.description: Derived from ancient variant of 烏(烏) (wū, "crow; black")
etymology.interpretation: The character 於(於) (yú, "at") evolved from an ancient variant of 烏(烏) (wū, "crow; black"), showing a historical phonetic borrowing unrelated to the components 方(方) (fāng, "square") or 㫃(㫃).

examples.chinese: 他出生於北京(他出生於北京)。
会议将於明天开始(會議將於明天開始)。
书籍陈列於图书馆(書籍陳列於圖書館)，方便读者查找(方便讀者查找)。
examples.pinyin: Shūjí chénliè yú túshūguǎn, fāngbiàn dúzhě cházhǎo。
examples.english: The books are displayed in the library, making it convenient for readers to find them.
